  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening of Comprehensive and Multisectoral Risk Management to Reduce Livelihoods Vulnerability of Communities Exposed to Multiple Natural and Man-Made Threats and Hidden Risks, Correlating Peri-Urban and Rural Areas in Bolivia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this project, IOM in Bolivia contributes through the generation of evidence in two prioritized municipalities in the Chiquitan&#xED;a region of Bolivia. In coordination with FAO, the Vice-Ministry of Civil Defense and authorities, a study is being developed which identifies the needs of the displaced and migrant population; explores the effect of migration from other regions in the prioritized municipalities; identifies the potential for migration from the prioritized municipalities, given the current circumstances related to climate change and environmental damage and the socioeconomic effects of the COVID-19 pandemic; and assesses the level of integration of migration into existing emergency prevention, preparedness and response policies. The evidence generated contributes to strengthening the capacities of local actors to address migration and displacement during emergency risk management, in order to strengthen the resilience of communities.</narrative>
  </description>
